cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically weakly supervised object localization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes attention mechanisms and dropout techniques, which are common in machine learning and deep learning research, suggesting that it could also fit into categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and experiments with image datasets, which could place it in categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
